         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">15/9/95 ¶  ¶ Allow me to ask, dear Professor Saccardo, whether in Italy any further measures are adopted against the devastations from Agaricus melleus, than those indicated by Hartig Kirchner, Franck...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.09.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Pier Saccardo</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Orto Botanico, Università degli Studi, Padua.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15/9/95</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me to ask, dear Professor Saccardo, whether in Italy any further measures are adopted against the devastations from <name key="Agaricus%20melleus">Agaricus melleus</name>, than those indicated by Hartig Kirchner, Franck and Tubeuf in their respective <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">volumes</hi>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M is most likely referring to Hartig (1889), especially pp. 179-84; Kirchner (1890); Frank (1880); and Tubeuf (1895), especially pp. 471-6. There are copies of all four works in the library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
               </note> Perhaps minor publications exist giving other means of coping with this destructive fungus; and it is also difficult here at the antipodes to know whether perhaps in journals new remedies have recently be<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>been?</p>
               </note> recommended.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A. melleus occurs here particularly in forests, and if rural plantations are formed in clearings of woodlands, then on some places the mycelium will destroy through strangling and sucking the roots destroy many kinds of trees, such as <name key="Juglans">Juglans</name>, <name key="Castanea">Castanea</name> &amp;c &amp;c. I shall therefore be most thankful to you for any special information which you may be able to afford from Italy.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In 'The honey coloured fungus', <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leader</seg> (Melbourne), 11 January 1896, p. 12, it was reported that 'by last mail Professor Saccardo, of Padua, the greatest mycologist of the present time, writes to the Government Botanist that it is found out that the <name key="Agaricus%20melleus">Agaricus melleus</name> destroys mulberry trees there' (letter not found).</p>
                  <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Can I send you anything specially from here.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Agaricus%20melleus">Agaricus melleus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Castanea">Castanea</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Juglans">Juglans</name>
            </p>
